items.title: Winter Weather Snarls Travel Across Northern Europe
items.description: Ice and cold disrupted airports and caused car accidents on Tuesday. More snow is expected in Amsterdam and Brussels on Wednesday.

items.title: Swiss Bar Hit by Deadly Fire Was Not Inspected for 6 Years, Authorities Say
items.description: Officials in Crans-Montana, the Swiss alpine resort town where a bar fire killed 40 people last week, are facing growing accusations of lax oversight.

items.title: The Unanswered Questions About Venezuela’s Environmental Future
items.description: The Trump administration has made no secret that it covets Venezuela’s oil reserves. What happens next could have serious implications for the planet.
